    "causal_summary": "The sk-code skill currently bundles JavaScript, CSS, and HTML style rules into five monolithic files under `references/webflow/standards/` (3,831 lines total), while the equivalent opencode-side reference tree is split per-language (`references/opencode/{javascript,typescript,python,shell,config,shared}/`). This asymmetry forces models to load mixed-language rule docs and increases the risk of mis-attributing rules across languages — a hypothesized cause of GPT 5.5's observed failure to apply correct CSS/JS comment style on Webflow tasks. This packet refactors the Webflow reference tree to mirror opencode's per-language layout and updates all cross-references and routing logic to match.",
